So I finally got this spell a few days ago.  Yesterday, I'm running through Dagnor's Cauldron, on my way to KK for the hell of it, and some noob asks for a lev.  I happily stop, mem Levitation, and go to buff this little gnome.  &quot;Your spell is to powerful for it's intended target&quot; or whatever the message is.  BAH!  A batwingless lev is too powerful for me to be buffing newbies with?!?  Come on!  I mean, I understand that KEI and Virtue are over the top, but levitate?  They really need to re-evaluate which spells are level restricted.  Besides, I had already deleted Levitate from my book, and I'm NOT going to go buy it and carry around batwings just to help out newbies.<br>
<br>
I also disagree with restricting most of the Hybrid's from casting parent class spells they didn't get until the 50s on lower level folks.  I mean when else are they going to get to use those spells?<br>
